Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 05, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab Stop saying "umm" If you don't have anything important to add, don't add anything. There is nothing wrong with being silent.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 05, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 2. Be confident. If you speak with enough confidence, people will trust what you say anyway. Build your confidence through repetition.'.

May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 3 Be quick and concise. hundreds of Nobody wants to listen to filler words that aren't used intentionally. Just get to the point quicker.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 05, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 4. Use silence. Instead of using filler words or running in circles when you don't have anything to say, stay silent. Silence is powerful when paired with clear conversations.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 05, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 5. Appropriate presentation. It has nothing to do with speech, but dressing accordingly can help prove your point and deliver your message accurately. Don't overdo it, just look appropriate for the convo.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on September 05, 2021 tagging @therobbiecrab. May be an image of text that says 'Robbie Crabtree @RobbieCrab 6. Deliver emotion. if you can control what emotions your audience feels through your words, you can get them to do anything. Happiness, sadness, anger, any emotion works.'.
